page.title: 07MISBOURNE, NUTLEY
page.content: A walk from Clockhouse Lane, Nutley to Cackle Street, Fairwarp. We started our walk from Clockhouse Lane. When we had got to the end of the lane we were on the forest. We noticed that it had been burned because it was black and brown. Further on, we saw some sandstone and soon we came to a stream which we jumped over. We walked up a very steep hill. While we were resting we saw a Common Blue and a Tortoiseshell butterfly. Beyond Misbourne, which is a trekking centre and sheep farm, we could count seven houses only. At the bottom of the hill we waded through another stream. We saw bracken, heather (Bog, Bell & Ling), tormentil and birds including a Kestrel and a skylark. In the forest valleys are called 'ghylls'.
